Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the DCS Platform Engineer position with ByteDance. I bring over three years of professional experience in building platforms, systems, and services for large-scale production environments, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade platform systems that directly reflect the technical depth this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected a platform service that translates natural-language intents into validated tool calls across 1,000+ production endpoints — requiring rigorous API contract design, input validation, and safe execution across distributed systems. To keep these systems production-ready, I designed a distributed observability layer using Langfuse and LangSmith with structured logging, tracing, and evaluation hooks to monitor networking systems and troubleshoot failures in fast-paced production environments. I also engineered a concurrent multi-agent orchestration system using LangChain and LangGraph for parallel systems execution, enabling scalable tool coordination across distributed workflows, and optimized web server routing to reduce latency by 60% and cloud services API costs by 50%. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to infrastructure that thousands of users rely on daily. I built an ITSM support chatbot using Python, LangChain and RAG with PostgreSQL vector store, reducing ticket resolution time by 20% and enabling natural language queries over ITOM documentation — giving me direct experience with IT Operation Management systems. I also designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis handling file operations across Google Cloud Storage, AWS S3, and MinIO through expiring signed URLs for asset and resource management in distributed systems, and contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform built with React, Spring Boot, and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications with highly available, stable, and high-performance services. Together, these roles have prepared me to build platforms, systems and services for internal and external teams to interact with large scale production systems and drive impact within an agile engineering team.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in GPU computing, Unix/Linux environments, and technical communication — skills that translate directly into the entrepreneurial mindset and relentless innovation ByteDance values through its "Always Day 1" culture. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted applied research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion using GPU acceleration with CUDA, PyTorch and LORA on Pace's HPC cluster for large software systems model training on Unix/Linux environments. I was responsible for managing the full model development lifecycle — from training runs to deploying highly available model inference using vLLM with Hugging Face, implementing web server optimization techniques for production-grade model delivery. Beyond building the systems myself, I led workshops on GPU programming with CUDA and Mojo, and on platform tooling with LangChain, LangGraph, and LangSmith for 50+ students. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly — directly mirroring the collaborative culture and knowledge-sharing that drives ByteDance's mission to inspire creativity and enrich life. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to the DCS platform team.

I have always been passionate about building highly available, stable, high-performance, and cost-effective computing resources and envision myself contributing my talent to furthering ByteDance's mission to inspire creativity and enrich life. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

